>>9481a2e1-5104-40e4-b5f2-1668d6710150
ZeroNet is software not service provider, it's impossible to force anything. Maybe if ZeroNet devs are soydevs they could somehow make life difficult for us, but denying us from using this technology is impossible. I can't find a CoC anywhere so it's a good sign. 

P2P will become a problem when governments will force ISPs to report usage of/or block services like this. We should prepare for that by building overlays on top of overlays. (fucking hell, someone just came honking with clown honk down the street while I was writing this, I'm not even kidding). We need to start hiding in normal traffic.
